metadata.name: Stone of the Avars (digital + physical)
metadata.description:
This stone is reflecting the theme used by local (central european) Avar tribe during the 6th century Anno Domini.
A local artist placed this stone in the area where the Avar burial ground was founded.

Note: with a digital ownership of the image you become the owner of the physical stone. The stone is ~90 cm high and, if you would like to, the artist can mark short word/initials in the back of the stone.
